               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Taz̲kirat al-shuʻarā' min taṣnīf-i Ṭāhir by Naṣrābādī, Muḥammad Ṭāhir‏
                  </summary>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_315-item1">
                     <author key="person_71054037" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/71054037/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Naṣrābādī, Muḥammad Ṭāhir‏</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">محمد طاهر نصرابادی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7415">Taz̲kirat al-shuʻarā' min taṣnīf-i Ṭāhir</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_7415">Taz̲kira-yi Naṣrābādī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7415">تذکره نصرابادی</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_7415">تذکرة الشعراء من تصنیف طاهر</title>
                     <colophon>
                        <locus>f.388b</locus> Colophon finished 16? Ṣafar 1101 4 – i.e. 1105. Chronogram (shud ākhar) gives 1105 A.H.</colophon>
                     <note>The work is complete. There are several minor variations in the order of entries in comparison to print editions and other manuscripts, and a limited number of poets are missing. Following the colophon, ff.389a-391a consist of an addendum on the poets of Yazd.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">سر سبزی نهال خامه از طراوت به بحر ذخار تذکار حمد صانعیست</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">زادیم در محنت و مردیم در وفا آن او سخن بود این آخر سخن</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>N. Bland “On the Earliest Persian Biography of Poets, by Muhammad Aufi, and on Some Other Works of the Class Called Tazkirat al-Shu’ara”. <title>Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland</title>. Vol. 9 (1847), pp. 111-176</bibl>
                        <bibl>A. Sprenger <title>A Catalogue of Arabic, Persian and Hindustany Manuscripts in the Libraries of the King of Oudh</title>. Calcutta (1854), pp. 88-108</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
